      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli): add exec approval recovery guidance (Fixes #53250)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #53250.\n\nWhen `host=node` exec approval is required but no approval UI is available, the CLI currently fails with a generic error:\n\n`exec denied: approval required (approval UI not available)`\n\nThat tells the operator something is wrong, but not what to do next. This patch makes the message actionable by naming two concrete recovery paths:\n- open the Control UI with `openclaw dashboard --no-open`\n- inspect pending approvals with `openclaw exec-approvals list`\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n```bash\ngit diff --check\n```\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed:\n- the node exec approval error should include actionable next steps instead of a dead-end “approval UI not available” message\n\nEnvironment tested:\n- local source checkout on this branch\n\nEvidence after the fix:\n- the thrown error string in `src/cli/nodes-cli/register.invoke.ts` now points to both the dashboard flow and the pending-approvals CLI\n\nObserved result:\n- users hitting this path now get concrete next steps in the error itself\n\nWhat was not tested:\n- a live node exec approval timeout/denial flow\n\n## Risk\n\nLow. This is a copy-only CLI error-message improvement with no behavior change in the approval flow itself.",
